    <body>
        <section name="Development">
        <subsection name="Publishing to java.net">
            <p>
                To publish to the java.net repository
            </p>
            <source>mvn deploy</source>
            <p>
                This goes via <a href="https://svn.dev.java.net/svn/maven2-repository/trunk/repository/>"><code>https://svn.dev.java.net/svn/maven2-repository/trunk/repository/</code></a>
                using <a href="https://wagon-svn.dev.java.net/">Wagon</a>. So you can jump onto the svn path above and
                watch the commit generated by Maven appear. Some scheduled task will then take it from the subversion
                repository to java.net proper (so there will likely be a lag before the public can download it).
            </p>
            <p>
                The subversion repository used by Wagon is authenticated, create a <code>~/.java.net</code> to allow
                an automatic process. See the <code>.java.net</code> file in tempus-fugit's source for an example.
            </p>
        </subsection>

        <subsection name="Maven">
            <p>
                Some favorites:
            </p>
            <source>mvn surefire-report:report-only</source>
            <p>
                To generate the awful Surefire report after running <code>mvn test</code>.
            </p>
        </subsection>

        </section>

    </body>
